obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (40167)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40167&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Delhi Apartment`
  line `Ownership Act, 1986.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the Union territory of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date as the Administrator may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (40168)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Application.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40168&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall apply to every apartment in a multi-storeyed`
  line `building which was constructed mainly for residential or commercial or such other purposes as may be`
  line `prescribed, by--`
  line
  line `(a) any group housing co-operative society; or`
  line
  line `(b) any other person or authority,`
  line
  line `before or after the commencement of this Act and on a free hold land, or a lease hold land, if the lease for`
  line `such land is for a period of thirty years or more:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where a building constructed, whether before or after the commencement of this Act,`
  line `on any land contains only two or three apartments, the owner of such building may, by a declaration duly`
  line `executed and registered under the provisions of the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), indicate his`
  line `intention to make the provisions of this Act applicable to such building, and on such declaration being`
  line `made, such owner shall execute and register a Deed of Apartment in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this Act, as if such owner were the promoter in relation to such building.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (40169)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40169&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Administrator" means the Administrator of the Union territory of Delhi appointed by the`
  line `President under article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) "allottee", in relation to an apartment, means the person to whom such apartment has been`
  line `allotted, sold or otherwise transferred by the promoter;`
  line
  line `(c) "apartment" means a part of any property, intended for any type of independent use, including`
  line `one or more rooms or enclosed spaces located on one or more floors or any part or parts thereof, in a`
  line `multi-storeyed building to be used for residence or office or for the practice of any profession, or for`
  line `the carrying on of any occupation, trade or business or for such other type of independent use as may`
  line `be prescribed, and with a direct exit to a public street, road or highway, or to a common area leading`
  line `to such street, road or highway, and includes any garage or room (whether or not adjacent to the`
  line `multi-storeyed building in which such apartment is located) provided by the promoter for use by the owner of such apartment for parking any vehicle or, as the case may be, for the residence of any`
  line `domestic aide employed in such apartment;`
  line
  line `(d) "apartment number" means the number, letter or combination thereof, designating an`
  line apartment;
  line
  line `(e) "apartment owner" means the person or persons owning an apartment and an undivided`
  line `interest in the common areas and facilities appurtenant to such apartment in the percentage specified`
  line `in the Deed of Apartment;`
  line
  line `(f) "Association of Apartment Owners",--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a multi-storeyed building not falling within sub-clause (ii), means all the`
  line `owners of the apartments therein;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of the multi-storeyed buildings in any area, designated as a block, pocket or`
  line `otherwise, means all the owners of the apartments in such block, pocket or other designated area,`
  line
  line `acting as a group in accordance with the bye-laws;`
  line
  line `(g) "authority" includes any authority constituted or established by or under any law for the time`
  line `being in force;`
  line
  line `(h) "Board" means the Board of Management of an Association of Apartment Owners elected by`
  line `its members under the bye-laws;`
  line
  line `(i) "bye-laws" means the bye-laws made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) "common areas and facilities", in relation to a multi-storeyed building, means--`
  line
  line `(i) the land on which such building is located and all easements, rights and appurtenances`
  line `belonging to the land and the building;`
  line
  line `(ii) the foundations, columns, girders, beams, supports, main walls, roofs, halls, corridors,`
  line `lobbies, stairs, stairways, fire-escapes and entrances and exits of the building;`
  line
  line `(iii) the basements, cellars, yards, gardens, parking areas, shopping centers, schools and`
  line `storage spaces;`
  line
  line `(iv) the premises for the lodging of janitors or persons employed for the management of the`
  line property;
  line
  line `(v) installations of central services, such as, power, light, gas, hot and cold water, heating,`
  line `refrigeration, air conditioning, incinerating and sewerage;`
  line
  line `(vi) the elevators, tanks, pumps, motors, fans, compressors, ducts and in general all apparatus`
  line `and installations existing for common use;`
  line
  line `(vii) such other community and commercial facilities as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(viii) all other parts of the property necessary or convenient to its existence, maintenance and`
  line `safety, or normally in common use;`
  line
  line `(k) "common expenses" means--`
  line
  line `(i) all sums lawfully assessed against the apartment owners by the Association of Apartment`
  line `Owners for meeting the expenses of administration, maintenance, repair or replacement of the`
  line `common areas and facilities;`
  line
  line `(ii) expenses declared as common expenses by the provisions of this Act or by the bye-laws,`
  line `or agreed upon by the Association of Apartment Owners;`
  line
  line `(l) "common profits" means the balance of all income, rents, profits and revenues from the`
  line `common areas and facilities remaining after the deduction of the common expenses;`
  line
  line `(m) "competent authority" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) a Secretary in the Delhi Administration, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the Vice-Chairman of the Delhi Development Authority, or`
  line
  line `(iii) the Land and Development Officer of the Central Government,`
  line `who may be authorised by the Administrator, by notification in the Official Gazette, to perform the`
  line `functions of the competent authority under this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) "Deed of Apartment" means the Deed of Apartment referred to in section 13;`
  line
  line `(o) "Delhi" means the Union territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(p) "joint family" means a Hindu undivided family, and in the case of other persons, a group or`
  line `unit, the members of which are by custom, joint in possession or residence;`
  line
  line `(q) "limited common areas and facilities" means those common areas and facilities which are`
  line `designated in writing by the promoter before the allotment, sale or other transfer of any apartment as`
  line `reserved for use of certain apartment or apartments to the exclusion of the other apartments;`
  line
  line `(r) "Manager" means the Manager of an Association of Apartment Owners appointed under the`
  line bye-laws;
  line
  line `(s) "multi-storeyed building" means a building constructed on any land, containing four or more`
  line `apartments, or two or more buildings in any area designated as a block, pocket or otherwise, each`
  line `containing two or more apartments, with a total of four or more apartments in all such buildings, and`
  line `includes a building containing two or three apartments in respect of which a declaration has been`
  line `made under the proviso to section 2;`
  line
  line `(t) "owner", in relation to an apartment, includes, for the purposes of this Act, a lessee of the land`
  line `on which the building containing such apartment has been constructed, where the lease of such land is`
  line `for a period of thirty years or more;`
  line
  line `(u) "person" includes a firm and a joint family, and also includes a group housing co-operative`
  line society;
  line
  line `(v) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(w) "promoter" means the authority, person or co-operative society, as the case may be, by which,`
  line `or by whom, any multi-storeyed building has been constructed;`
  line
  line `(x) "property" means the land, the multi-storeyed building, all improvement and structures`
  line `thereon, and all easements, rights and appurtenances belonging thereto, and all articles of personal`
  line `property intended for use in connection therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (40170)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Ownership of apartments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40170&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person to whom any apartment is allotted, sold or`
  line `otherwise transferred by the promoter, on or after the commencement of this Act, shall, save as otherwise`
  line `provided in section 6, and subject to the other provisions of this Act, be entitled to the exclusive`
  line `ownership and possession of the apartment so allotted, sold or otherwise transferred to him.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person to whom any apartment was allotted, sold or otherwise transferred by the promoter`
  line `before the commencement of this Act shall, save as otherwise provided under section 6 and subject to the`
  line `other provisions of this Act, be entitled, on and from such commencement, to the exclusive ownership`
  line `and possession of the apartment so allotted, sold or otherwise transferred to him.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person who becomes entitled to the exclusive ownership and possession of an apartment`
  line `under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be entitled to such percentage of undivided interest in the`
  line `common areas and facilities as may be specified in the Deed of Apartment and such percentage shall be`
  line `computed by taking, as a basis, the value of the apartment in relation to the value of the property.`
  line
  line `(4) (a) The percentage of the undivided interest of each apartment owner in the common areas and`
  line `facilities shall have a permanent character, and shall not be altered without the written consent of all the`
  line `apartment owners.`
  line
  line `(b) The percentage of the undivided interest in the common areas and facilities shall not be separated`
  line `from the apartment to which it appertains and shall be deemed to be conveyed or encumbered with the`
  line `apartment, even though such interest is not expressly mentioned in the conveyance or other instrument.`
  line
  line `(5) The common areas and facilities shall remain undivided and no apartment owner or any other`
  line `person shall bring any action for partition or division of any part thereof, and any covenant to the contrary`
  line `shall be void.`
  line
  line `(6) Each apartment owner may use the common areas and facilities in accordance with the purposes`
  line `for which they are intended without hindering or encroaching upon the lawful rights of the other`
  line `apartment owners.`
  line
  line `(7) The necessary work relating to maintenance, repair and replacement of the common areas and`
  line `facilities and the making of any additions or improvements thereto, shall be carried out only in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act and the bye-laws.`
  line
  line `(8) The Association of Apartment Owners shall have the irrevocable right, to be exercised by the`
  line `Board or Manager, to have access to each apartment from time to time during reasonable hours for the`
  line `maintenance, repairs or replacement of any of the common areas or facilities therein, or accessible`
  line `therefrom, or for making emergency repairs therein necessary to prevent damage to the common areas`
  line `and facilities or to any other apartment or apartments.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (40171)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Apartment to be heritable and transferable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40171&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 6, each`
  line `apartment, together with the undivided interest in the common areas and facilities appurtenant to such`
  line `apartment, shall, for all purposes constitute as a heritable and transferable immovable property within the`
  line `meaning of any law for the time being in force, and accordingly, an apartment owner may transfer his`
  line `apartment and the percentage of undivided interest in the common areas and facilities appurtenant to such`
  line `apartment by way of sale, mortgage, lease, gift, exchange or in any other manner whatsoever in the same`
  line `manner, to the same extent and subject to the same rights, privileges, obligations, liabilities,`
  line `investigations, legal proceedings, remedy and to penalty, forfeiture or punishment as any other`
  line `immovable property or make a bequest of the same under the law applicable to the transfer and`
  line `succession of immovable property:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the allotment, sale or other transfer of any apartment has been made by any`
  line `group housing co-operative society in favour of any member thereof, the transferability of such apartment`
  line `and all other matters shall be regulated by the law applicable to such group housing co-operative society.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (40172)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Ownership of apartment subject to conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40172&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Where any allotment, sale or other transfer of`
  line `any apartment has been made, whether before or after the commencement of this Act, in pursuance of any`
  line `promise of payment, or part payment, of the consideration thereof, the allottee or transferee, as the case`
  line `may be, shall not become entitled to the ownership and possession of that apartment on to a percentage of`
  line `undivided interest in the common areas and facilities apurtenant to such apartment, until full payment has`
  line `been made of the consideration thereof together with interest, if any due thereon, and where any such`
  line `allottee or transferee has been inducted into the possession of such apartment or any part thereof in`
  line `pursuance of such allotment or transfer, he shall, until the full payment of the consideration has been`
  line `made, continue to remain in possession thereof on the same terms and conditions on which he was so`
  line `inducted into possession of such apartment of part thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (40173)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Compliance with the covenants and bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40173&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Each apartment owner shall comply strictly with`
  line `the bye-laws and with the covenants, conditions and restrictions set forth in the Deed of Apartment, and`
  line `failure to comply with any of them shall be a ground for action to recover sums due for damages, or for`
  line `injunctive relief, or both, by the Manager or Board on behalf of the Association of Apartment Owners, or,`
  line `in a proper case, by an aggrieved apartment owner.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (40174)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Right of re-entry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40174&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any land is given on lease by a person (hereafter in this section`
  line `referred to as the lessor) to another person (hereafter in this section referred to as the lessee, which term`
  line `shall include a person in whose favour a sub-lease of such land has been granted), and any multi-storeyed`
  line
  line `building has been constructed on such lease-hold land by the lessee or by any other person authorised by`
  line `him or claiming through him, such lessee shall grant in respect of the land as many sub-leases as there are`
  line `apartments in such multi-storeyed building and shall execute separate deeds of sub-lease in respect of`
  line `such land in favour of each apartment owner,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a multi-storeyed building constructed before the commencement of this Act,`
  line `within three months from such commencement, or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a multi-storeyed building constructed after the commencement of this Act,`
  line `within three months from the date on which the possession of any apartment in such multi-storeyed`
  line `building is delivered to him:`
  line
  line `Provident that no sub-lease in respect of any land shall be granted except on the same terms and`
  line `conditions on which the lease in respect of the land has been granted by the lessor and no additional terms`
  line `and conditions shall be imposed by the lessee except with the previous approval of the lessor.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the lessee has any reason to suspect that there had been any breach of the terms and`
  line `conditions of the sub-lease referred to in sub-section (1), he may himself inspect the land on which the`
  line `multi-storeyed building containing the concerned apartment has been constructed, or may authorise one or`
  line `more persons to inspect such land and make a report as to whether there had been any breach of the terms`
  line `and conditions of any sub-lease in respect of such land and, if so, the nature and extent of such breach,`
  line `and for this purpose, it shall be lawful for the lessee or any person authorised by him to enter into, and to`
  line `be in, the land in relation to which such breach has been or is suspected to have been committed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the lessee or any person authorised by him makes an inspection of the land referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), he shall record in writing his findings on such inspection a true copy of which shall be`
  line `furnished to the apartment owner by whom such breach of the terms and conditions of sub-lease in`
  line `respect of the land appurtenant to the apartment owned by him has been committed (hereinafter referred`
  line `to as the defaulting apartment owner) and where such findings indicate that there has been any breach of`
  line `the terms and conditions of the sub-lease in respect of such land, the lessee may, by a notice in writing,`
  line `require the defaulting apartment owner to refrain from committing any breach of the terms and conditions`
  line `of the sub-lease in respect of such land, or to pay in lieu thereof such composition fees as may be`
  line `specified in the notice in accordance with such scales of composition fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The defaulting apartment owner who is aggrieved by any notice served on him by the lessee under`
  line `sub-section (3) may, within thirty days from the date of service of such notice, prefer an appeal to the`
  line `Court of the District Judge having jurisdiction (hereinafter referred to as the District Court), either`
  line `challenging the finding of the lessee or any person authorised by him or disputing the amount of`
  line `composition fees as specified in the notice, and the District Court may, after giving the parties a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard, confirm, alter or reverse those findings or may confirm, reduce or`
  line `increase the amount of composition fees or set aside the notice.`
  line
  line `(5) Where, on the breach of any terms and conditions of any sub-lease in respect of any land, any`
  line `composition fees become payable, the defaulting apartment owner shall be deemed to have been guilty of`
  line `such breach and in default of payment thereof it shall be lawful for the lessee to recover the amount of the`
  line `composition fees from the defaulting apartment owner as an arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any composition fees are paid whether in pursuance of the notice served under`
  line `sub-section (3) or in accordance with the decision of the District Court or a higher court on appeal, no`
  line `further action shall be taken by the lessee for the breach of the terms and conditions of the sub-lease in`
  line `respect of the land in relation to which payment of such composition fees has been made.`
  line
  line `(7) If the defaulting apartment owner omits or fails to refrain from committing any breach of the`
  line `terms and conditions of the sub-lease in respect of the land or, as the case may be, omits or fails to pay the`
  line `composition fees in lieu thereof--`
  line
  line `(i) in accordance with the notice issued by the lessee under sub-section (3), or`
  line
  line `(ii) where the findings of the lessee or the person authorised to inspect the land about any breach`
  line `of the terms and conditions of any sub-lease in respect of the land or the amount of composition fees`
  line
  line `specified in the notice issued by the lessee are altered by the District Court on appeal or by any higher`
  line `court on further appeal, in accordance with the decision of the District Court or such higher court, as`
  line `the case may be,`
  line
  line `the lessee shall be entitled,--`
  line
  line `(a) where no appeal has been preferred under sub-section (4), within sixty days from the date of`
  line `service of the notice under sub-section (3), or`
  line
  line `(b) where an appeal has been preferred under sub-section (4), within sixty days from the date on`
  line `which the appeal is finally disposed of by the District Court or, where any further appeal is preferred`
  line `to a higher court, by such higher court,`
  line
  line `to exercise the right of re-entry in respect of the undivided interest of the lessee in the land appurtenant to`
  line `the apartment owned by the defaulting apartment owner, and where such right of re-entry cannot be`
  line `exercised except by the ejectment of the defaulting apartment owner from his apartment, such right of`
  line `re-entry shall include a right to eject the defaulting apartment owner from the concerned apartment:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such ejectment shall be made unless the defaulting apartment owner has been paid`
  line `by the lessee such amount as compensation for such ejectment as may be determined in accordance with`
  line `the prescribed scales of compensation.`
  line
  line `(8) No appeal preferred under sub-section (4) shall be admitted, unless twenty-five per cent. of the`
  line `composition fees specified in the notice served on the defaulting apartment owner has been deposited to`
  line `the credit of the District Court in savings bank account to be opened by the District Court in any branch of`
  line `an approved bank:`
  line
  line `Provided that the District Court may, on sufficient cause being shown, either remit or reduce the`
  line `amount of such deposit, and the interest accruing on such deposit, shall enure to the credit of defaulting`
  line `apartment owner by whom such deposit has been made:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the amount of such deposit together with the interest due thereon shall be`
  line `distributed by the District Court in accordance with the decision in such appeal, or where any further`
  line `appeal has been preferred against such decision, in accordance with the decision in such further appeal.`
  line
  line `(9) The defaulting apartment owner, who is aggrieved by the amount offered to be paid to him under`
  line `the proviso to sub-section (7) as compensation for ejectment from his apartment may, within thirty days`
  line `from the date of such offer, prefer an appeal to the District Court and the District Court may, after giving`
  line `the parties a reasonable opportunity of being heard, maintain increase or reduce the amount of`
  line compensation.
  line
  line `(10) On the ejectment of the defaulting apartment owner from the apartment under sub-section (7),`
  line `the lessee by whom such ejectment has been made may a fresh allotment of the concerned apartment to`
  line `any other person on such terms and conditions as he may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the consideration for such fresh allotment shall not be more than the amount which has`
  line `been paid to the defaulting apartment owner as compensation.`
  line
  line `(11) Where any lessee omits or fails to take any action either in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) or sub-section (7), the lessor may, in the first instance, require the`
  line `lessee by a notice in writing to take action against the defaulting apartment owner under sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (3) or, as the case may be, under sub-section (7), within a period of ninety days from the date`
  line `of service of such notice, and in the event of the omission or failure of the lessee to do so within such`
  line `period, the lessor may himself take action as contained in sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) or`
  line `sub-section (7), and the provisions of sub-section (4) to sub-section (6) and sub-section (8) to sub-section`
  line `(10), shall, as far as may be, apply to any action taken by him as if such action had been taken by the`
  line lessee.
  line
  line `(12) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that no work in any apartment by the owner`
  line `thereof shall be deemed to be a breach of the terms of the sub-lease in respect of the land on which the`
  line `multi-storeyed building containing such apartment has been constructed unless the work is prohibited by`
  line `section 11.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "approved bank" means the State Bank of India constituted under`
  line `section 3 of the State Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955), or a subsidiary bank constituted under`
  line `section 3 of the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959), or a corresponding new`
  line `bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings)`
  line `Act, 1970 (5 of 1970) or a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking Companies`
  line `(Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (40195)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Purchasers or persons taking lease of apartments from apartment owners to execute an undertaking.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40195&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), or`
  line `in any other law for the time being in the force, any person acquiring any apartment from any apartment`
  line `owner by gift, exchange, purchase or otherwise, or taking lease of an apartment from an apartment owner`
  line `for a period of thirty years or more, shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of the said apartment, be subject to the provisions of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) execute and register an instrument in such form, in such manner and within such period as`
  line `may be prescribed giving an undertaking to comply with the covenants, conditions and restrictions,`
  line `subject to which such apartment is owned by the apartment owner aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (40176)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Benamidar of the apartment to be deemed to be the real owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40176&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `If any apartment is acquired`
  line `by any person, whether by allotment, sale or otherwise with the consideration thereof paid or provided by`
  line `another person, the acquirer shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the Transfer of Property`
  line `Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), or in the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of 1882) or in any other law for the time being`
  line `in force, be deemed to be the real owner of such apartment, and no court shall entertain any claim of the`
  line `person paying or providing such consideration for title to such apartment on the ground that the`
  line `acquisition of the apartment was made on behalf of such person or on behalf of someone through whom`
  line `such person claims.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (40177)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Certain works prohibited.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40177&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `No apartment owner shall do any work which would be prejudicial`
  line `to the soundness or safety of the property or reduce the value thereof or impair any easement or`
  line `hereditament or shall add any material structure or excavate any additional basement or cellar without`
  line `first obtaining the consent of all the other apartment owners.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, reference to apartment owners shall be construed, in relation to a`
  line `multi-storeyed building in any block, pocket or other designated area, the apartment owners of the`
  line `concerned multi-storeyed building in such block, pocket or other designated area.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (40178)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Encumbrances against apartments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40178&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner of each apartment may create any`
  line `encumbrance, only against the apartment owned by him and the percentage of the undivided interest in`
  line `the common areas and facilities appurtenant to such apartment in the same manner and to the same extent`
  line `as may be created in relation to any other separate parcel of property subject to individual ownership:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such encumbrance is created, the apartment in relation to which such`
  line `encumbrance has been created shall not be partitioned or sub-divided.`
  line
  line `(2) No labour performed or material furnished with the consent, or at the request, of an apartment`
  line `owner or his agent or his contractor or sub-contractor, shall be the basis for a charge or any encumbrance`
  line `under the provisions of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), against the apartment or property`
  line `of any other apartment owner not expressly consenting to, or requesting the same, except that such`
  line `express consent shall be deemed to be given by the other apartment owner in the case of emergency`
  line `repairs thereto.`
  line
  line `(3) The labour performed and material furnished for the common areas and facilities, if duly`
  line `authorised by the Association of Apartment Owners in accordance with the provisions of this Act or the`
  line `bye-laws, shall be deemed to be performed or furnished with the express consent of each apartment owner`
  line `and shall be the basis for a charge or encumbrance under the Act aforesaid against each of the apartments`
  line `and shall be subject to the provisions of sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(4) In the event of a charge or any encumbrance against two or more apartments becoming effective,`
  line `the apartment owners of the separate apartments may remove their apartments and the percentage of undivided interest in the common areas and facilities appurtenant to such apartments from the charge or`
  line `encumbrance on payment of the fractional or proportional amounts attributable to each of the apartments`
  line `affected and on such payment, the apartment and the percentage of undivided interest in the common`
  line `areas and facilities appurtenant thereto shall be free of the charge or encumbrance so removed:`
  line
  line `Provided that such partial payment shall not prevent the person having a charge or any of the`
  line `encumbrances from proceeding to enforce the rights in relation to the amount not so paid, against any`
  line `other apartment and the percentage of undivided interest in the common areas and facilities appurtenant to`
  line `such apartment.`
  line
  line `(5) On any such payment, discharge on other satisfaction, referred to in sub-section (4), the apartment`
  line `and the percentage of undivided interest in the common areas and facilities appurtenant thereto shall be`
  line `free and clear of the charge or encumbrance, so paid, satisfied or discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (40179)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Contents of Deed of Apartment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40179&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any allotment, sale or other transfer of any`
  line `apartment is made, the promoter shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an allotment, sale or other transfer made after the commencement of this Act,`
  line `within three months from the date of such allotment, sale or other transfer, or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any allotment, sale or other transfer made before the commencement of this Act,`
  line `within six months from the date of such commencement,`
  line
  line `execute a Deed of Apartment containing the following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the name of the allottee,`
  line
  line `(ii) description of the land on which the building and the common areas and facilities are located,`
  line `and whether the land is free-hold or lease-hold, and if lease-hold, the period of such lease,`
  line
  line `(iii) a set of floor plans of the multi-storeyed building showing the lay-out and location, number`
  line `of apartments and bearing a verified statement of an architect certifying that it is an accurate copy of`
  line `the portions of the plans of the building as filed with, and approved by, the local authority within the`
  line `jurisdiction of which the building is located,`
  line
  line `(iv) description of the multi-storeyed building, stating the number of storeys and basements, the`
  line `number of apartments in that building and the principal materials of which it is constructed,`
  line
  line `(v) the apartment number, or statement of the location of the apartment, its approximate area,`
  line `number and dimension of rooms, and immediate common area to which it has access, and any other`
  line `data necessary for its proper identification,`
  line
  line `(vi) description of the common areas and facilities and the percentage of undivided interest`
  line `appertaining to the apartment in the common areas and facilities,`
  line
  line `(vii) description of the limited common areas and facilities, if any, stating to which apartments`
  line `their use is reserved,`
  line
  line `(viii) value of the property and of each apartment, and a statement that the apartment and such`
  line `percentage of undivided interest are not encumbered in any number whatsoever on the date of`
  line `execution of the Deed of Apartment,`
  line
  line `(ix) statement of the purposes for which the building and each of the apartments are intended and`
  line `restricted as to use,`
  line
  line `(x) the name of the person to receive service of process, together with the particulars of the`
  line `residence or place of business of such person,`
  line
  line `(xi) provision as to the percentage of votes by the apartment owners which shall be determinative`
  line `of whether to rebuild, repair, restore, or sell the property in the event of damage or destruction of all`
  line `or any part of the property:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority may, if it is satisfied that the promoter was prevented by`
  line `sufficient cause from executing the Deed of Apartment in relation to any apartment within the period of`
  line `three months, or six months as the case may be, permit the promoter to execute such Deed of Apartment`
  line `within such further period, not exceeding six months, as it may specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The promoter shall--`
  line
  line `(a) file in the office of the competent authority; and`
  line
  line `(b) deliver to the concerned allottee or transferee, as the case may be,`
  line
  line `a certified copy of each Deed of Apartment as registered under section 14.`
  line
  line `(3) Whenever may transfer of any apartment is made by the owner thereof, whether by sale, lease,`
  line `mortgage, exchange, gift or otherwise, the transferor shall deliver to the transferee the certified copy of`
  line `the Deed of Apartment delivered to him under sub-section (2) after making an endorsement thereon as to`
  line `the name, address and other particulars of the transferee, to enable the transferee to get the endorsement`
  line `on the certified copy of the Deed of Apartment registered in accordance with the provisions of section 14.`
  line
  line `(4) Whenever any succession takes place to any apartment or part thereof, the successor shall, within`
  line `a period of six months from the date of such succession, make an application to the competent authority`
  line `for recording such succession on the certified copy of the Deed of Apartment in relation to the concerned`
  line `apartment, and, if there is any dispute as to the succession to the apartment, the competent authority shall`
  line `decide be same, and for this purpose, such authority shall have the powers of a civil court, while trying a`
  line `suit, and its decision shall have effect of a decree and shall be appealable as if it were a decree passed by`
  line `the principal civil court of original jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(5) Whenever any succession to an apartment has been recorded by the competent authority under`
  line `sub-section (4), such authority shall send a true copy of such record, to the concerned Registrar for`
  line `registration thereof in accordance with the provisions of section 14.`
  line
  line `(6) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the provisions of this section shall be in`
  line `addition to and not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law, for the time being in force, relating`
  line `to the transfer of immovable property.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (40180)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Registration of Deed of Apartment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40180&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Deed of Apartment and every endorsement`
  line `thereon relating to the transfer of the apartment shall be deemed to be a document which is compulsorily`
  line `registrable under the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908) and shall be registered with the Registrar`
  line `accordingly, and the words and expressions used in this section but not defined in this Act, shall have the`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in the Registration Act, 1908.`
  line
  line `(2) In all registration offices, a book called "Register of Deeds or Apartments under the Delhi`
  line `Apartment Ownership Act, 1986" and an index relating thereto shall be kept in such form and shall`
  line `contain such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Whenever any endorsement on a Deed of Apartment is registered, the concerned Registrar shall`
  line `forward a certified copy thereof to the competent authority to enable that authority to make necessary`
  line `entries in the certified copy of the concerned Deed of Apartment filed with it under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 13.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person acquiring any apartment shall be deemed to have notice of the contents of the Deed of`
  line `Apartment and the endorsement, if any, thereon as from the date of its registration under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (40181)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Association of Apartment Owners and bye-laws relating thereto.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40181&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be an`
  line `Association of Apartment Owners for the administration of the affairs in relation to the apartments and`
  line `the property appertaining thereto and for the management of common areas and facilities:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any area has been demarcated for the construction of multi-storeyed buildings,`
  line `whether such area is called a block or pocket or by any other name, there shall be a single Association of`
  line `Apartment Owners in such demarcated area.`
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette, frame model bye-laws in`
  line `accordance with which the property referred to in sub-section (1) shall be administered by the Association`
  line `of Apartment Owners and every such Association shall, at its first meeting, make its bye-laws in`
  line `accordance with the model bye-laws so framed, and in making its bye-laws the Association of Apartment`
  line `Owners shall not make any departure from, variation of, addition to, or omission from, the model`
  line `bye-laws aforesaid except with the prior approval of the Administrator and no such approval shall be`
  line `given if, in the opinion of the Administrator, such departure, variation, addition or omission will have the`
  line `effect of altering the basic structure of the model bye-laws framed by him.`
  line
  line `(3) The model bye-laws framed under sub-section (2) shall provide for the following, among other`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which the Association of Apartment Owners is to be formed;`
  line
  line `(b) the election, from among apartment owners, of a Board of Management by the members of`
  line `the Association of Apartment Owners;`
  line
  line `(c) the number of apartment owners constituting the Board, the composition of the Board and that`
  line `one-third of members of the Board shall retire annually;`
  line
  line `(d) the powers and duties of the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) the honorarium, if any, of the members of the Board;`
  line
  line `(f) the method of removal from office of the members of the Board;`
  line
  line `(g) the powers of the Board to engage the service of a Manager;`
  line
  line `(h) delegation of powers and duties of the Board to such Manager;`
  line
  line `(i) method of calling meetings of the Association of Apartment Owners and the number of`
  line `members of such Association who shall constitute a quorum for such meetings;`
  line
  line `(j) election of a President of the Association of Apartment Owners from among the apartment`
  line `owners, who, shall preside over the meetings of the Board and of the Association of Apartment`
  line Owners;
  line
  line `(k) election of a Secretary to the Association of Apartment Owners from among the apartment`
  line `owners, who shall be an ex officio member of the Board and shall keep two separate minutes books,`
  line `one for the Association of Apartment Owners and the other for the Board, pages of each of which`
  line `shall be consecutively numbered and authenticated by the President of the Association of Apartment`
  line `Owners, and shall record, in the respective minutes books, the resolutions adopted by the Association`
  line `of Apartment Owners or the Board, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(l) election of a Treasurer from among the apartment owners, who shall keep the financial records`
  line `of the Association of Apartment Owners as also of the Board;`
  line
  line `(m) maintenance, repair and replacement of the common areas and facilities and payment`
  line therefor;
  line
  line `(n) manner of collecting from the apartment owners or any other occupant of apartments, share of`
  line `the common expenses;`
  line
  line `(o) resignation and removal of persons employed for the maintenance, repair and replacement of`
  line `the common areas and facilities;`
  line
  line `(p) restrictions with regard to the use and maintenance of the apartments and the use of the`
  line `common areas and facilities, as may be necessary to prevent unreasonable interference in the use of`
  line `each apartment and of the common areas and facilities by the several apartment owners;`
  line
  line `(q) any matter which may be required by the Administrator to be provided for in the bye-laws for`
  line `the proper or better administration of the property;`
  line
  line `(r) such other matters as are required to be, or may be, provided for in the bye-laws.`
  line
  line `(4) The bye-laws framed under sub-section (2) may also contain provisions, not inconsistent with`
  line `this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) enabling the Board to retain certain areas of the building for commercial purposes and to grant`
  line `lease of the areas so retained, and to apply the proceeds of such lease for the reduction of the common`
  line `expenses for maintaining the building, common areas and facilities, and if any surplus is left after`
  line `meeting such expenses, to distribute such surplus to the apartment owners as income;`
  line
  line `(b) relating to the audit of the accounts of the Association of Apartment Owners and of the Board,`
  line `and of the administration of the property;`
  line
  line `(c) specifying the times at which and the manner in which annual general meetings and special`
  line `general meetings of the Association of Apartment Owners shall be held and conducted;`
  line
  line `(d) specifying the time at which and the manner in which, the annual report relating to the`
  line `activities of the Association of Apartment Owners shall be submitted;`
  line
  line `(e) specifying the manner in which the income derived and expenditure incurred by the`
  line `Association of Apartment Owners shall be dealt with, or as the case may be, accounted for.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (40182)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Insurance.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40182&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board or Manager--`
  line
  line `(a) shall have, if requested so to do by a mortgagee having a first mortgage covering an`
  line `apartment, the authority to, and`
  line
  line `(b) shall, if required so to do by the bye-laws or by a majority of the apartment owners,`
  line
  line `obtain insurance for the property against loss or damage by fire or other hazards under such terms and for`
  line `such amounts as shall be so requested or required.`
  line
  line `(2) Such insurance coverage shall be written on the property in the name of such Board or Manager as`
  line `trustee for each of the apartment owners in the percentages specified in the bye-laws.`
  line
  line `(3) The premia payable in respect of every such insurance shall be common expenses.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-sections (1) to (3) shall be without prejudice to the right of each of the`
  line `apartment owner to insure his own apartment for his benefit.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (40183)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Disposition of property, destruction or damage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40183&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `If within sixty days of the date of damage or`
  line `destruction to all, or part of any property, or within such further time as the competent authority may,`
  line `having regard to the circumstances of the case, allow, the Association of Apartment Owners does not`
  line `determine to repair, reconstruct or re-build such property, then, and in that event,--`
  line
  line `(a) the property shall be deemed to be owned in common by the apartment owners;`
  line
  line `(b) the undivided interest in the property owned in common, which shall appertain to each`
  line `apartment owner, shall be the percentage of the undivided interest previously owned by such owner in`
  line `the common areas and facilities;`
  line
  line `(c) any incumbrances affecting any of the apartments shall be deemed to be transferred in`
  line `accordance with the existing priority to the percentage of the undivided interest of the apartment`
  line `owner in the property;`
  line
  line `(d) the property shall be subject to an action for partition at the suit of any apartment owner in`
  line `which event, the net proceeds of sale together with the net proceeds of the insurance on the property,`
  line `if any, shall be considered as one fund and shall be divided amongst all the apartment owners in the`
  line `percentage equal to the percentage of undivided interest owned by each apartment owner in the`
  line `property after paying out, all the respective shares of the apartment owners to the extent sufficient for`
  line `the purpose and all charges on the undivided interest in the property owned by each apartment owner.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (40184)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Action.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40184&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the rights of any apartment owner, action may be brought by`
  line `the Board of Manager, in either case in the discretion of the Board on behalf of two or more of the`
  line `apartment owners as their respective interest may appear, with respect to any cause of action relating to`
  line `the common areas and facilities or more than one apartment.`
  line
  line `(2) The service of process on two or more apartment owners in any action relating to the common`
  line `areas and facilities or more than one apartment may be made on the person, designated in the bye-laws to`
  line `receive service of process.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (40185)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Common profits, common expenses and other matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40185&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The common profits of the`
  line `property shall be distributed among, and the common expenses shall be charged to, the apartment owners`
  line `according to the percentage of the undivided interest of the apartment owners in the common areas and`
  line facilities.
  line
  line `(2) Where the apartment owner is not in the occupation of the apartment owned by him, the common`
  line `expenses payable by such apartment owner may be recovered from the person in the occupation of the`
  line apartment.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (40194)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Apartment owner not to be exempt from liability for contribution by waiver of the use of the common areas and facilities`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40194&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `No apartment owner may exempt himself from liability for his`
  line `contribution towards the common expenses by waiver of the use of enjoyment of any of the common`
  line `areas and facilities, or by the abandonment of his apartment.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (40187)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Common expenses to be a charge on the apartment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40187&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `All sums assessed by the Association of`
  line `Apartment Owners, but unpaid for the share of the common expenses chargeable to any apartment, shall`
  line `constitute a charge on such apartment prior to all other charges except only--`
  line
  line `(i) the charge, if any, on the apartment for payment of Government and municipal taxes; and`
  line
  line `(ii) all the sums unpaid on a first mortgage of the apartment.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (40188)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Separate assessments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40188&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any law`
  line `relating to local authorities, each apartment and its percentage of undivided interest in the common areas`
  line `and facilities appurtenant to such apartment (including an apartment in respect of which the provisions of`
  line `this Act were applied under the proviso to section 2) shall be deemed to be separate property for the`
  line `purpose of assessment of tax on lands and buildings leviable under such law and shall be assessed and`
  line `taxed accordingly; and for this purpose a local authority shall make suitable regulations to carry out the`
  line `provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Neither the multi-storeyed building nor the property nor the common areas and facilities referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1), shall be deemed to be separate properties for the purpose of the levy of such taxes.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (40189)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Joint and several liability of vendor, etc., for unpaid common expenses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40189&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Upon the sale,`
  line `bequest or other transfer of an apartment, the purchaser of the apartment or the grantee or legatee or the`
  line `transferee, as the case may be, shall be jointly and severally liable with the vendor or the transferor for`
  line `all unpaid assessments against the vendor or transferor for his share of the common expenses up to the`
  line `time of the sale, bequest or other transfer, without prejudice to the right of the purchaser, grantee, legatee`
  line `or transferee to recover from the vendor or the transferor any amount paid by the purchaser, grantee,`
  line `legatee or transferee therefor.`
  line
  line `(2) Any purchaser, grantee, legatee or transferee referred to in sub-section (1) shall be entitled to a`
  line `statement from the Board or Manager setting forth the amount of the unpaid assessment against the`
  line `vendor or transferor, as the case may be, and such purchaser, grantee, legatee or transferee shall not be`
  line `liable for, nor shall the apartment be sold subject to a charge for any unpaid share of common expenses`
  line `against such apartment accrued prior to such sale, bequest or other transfer, in excess of the amount set`
  line `forth in the statement.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (40190)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Act to be binding on apartment owners, tenants, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40190&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being`
  line `in force or in any contract, undertaking or other instrument and all apartment owners, tenants of owners,`
  line `employees of owners and tenants, or any other person who may, in any manner, use the property or any`
  line `part thereof to which this Act applies, shall be subject to the provisions of this Act and the bye-laws and`
  line `the rules made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall affect the right, title or interest acquired by`
  line `any allottee or other person in common areas and facilities from any promoter on or before the 28th day`
  line `of February, 1986.`
  line
  line `(2) All agreements, divisions and determinations lawfully made by the Association of Apartment`
  line `Owners in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the bye-laws shall be deemed to be binding on`
  line `all apartment owners.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (40191)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to exempt stamp duty, registration fee and court fees and power to refund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40191&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, reduce or remit, whether prospectively`
  line `or retrospectively from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the stamp duty with which, under any law relating to stamp duty for the time being in force,`
  line `instruments or documents executed by or on behalf of a promoter, apartment owner or Association of`
  line `Apartment Owners relating to any of the purposes of this Act are respectively chargeable;`
  line
  line `(b) any fee payable by or on behalf of any promoter, apartment owner or Association of`
  line `Apartment Owners in relation to instruments or documents referred to in clause (a) under any law`
  line `relating to registration of documents or to court fees, for the time being in force,`
  line
  line `and which the Central Government is competent to levy.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may refund the amount of any duty or fee paid in pursuance of any law`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) in such circumstances, to such extent and subject to such terms and`
  line `conditions, if any, as that Government may, by order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (40192)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Removal of doubts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40192&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the provisions of the`
  line `Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), shall, in so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions`
  line `of this Act, apply to the transfer of any apartment, together with its undivided interest in the common`
  line `areas and facilities appurtenant thereto, made by the owner of such apartment, whether such transfer is`
  line `made by sale, lease, mortgage, exchange, gift or otherwise, as they apply to the transfer of any immovable`
  line property.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (40193)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406&sectionId=40193&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00023_198658_1517807326406
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the purposes, other than the purposes specified in section 2, for which any multi-storeyed`
  line `building may be utilised;`
  line
  line `(b) the type of independent uses, other than the uses specified in clause (c) of section 3, which`
  line `may be made of an apartment;`
  line
  line `(c) the community and commercial facilities which may be included in common areas and`
  line `facilities under sub-clause (vii) of clause (j) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) the scales of composition fees which may be paid under section 8 for the breach of the terms`
  line `and conditions of any lease or sub-lease;`
  line
  line `(e) the scales in accordance with which compensation, to be paid for the ejectment of an`
  line `apartment owner from his apartment, shall be determined as required by sub-section (7) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(f) the form and manner in which, and the period within which, an instrument referred to in`
  line `clause (b) of section 9, shall be executed and registered;`
  line
  line `(g) the form in which the Register of Deeds of Apartments under the Delhi Apartment Ownership`
  line `Act, 1986 and the index relating thereto shall be kept and the particulars which such Register shall`
  line `contain as required by sub-section (2) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule, or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
